    {
        "content": "<p>Motivated by <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"310045\">@Eric Wieser</span> 's comment in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/14296\">#14296</a>.</p>",
        "id": 283230849,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1653224139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's <code>0 &lt; n</code> vs <code>n ≠ 0</code> all over again. So we would like to simplify towards <code>a &lt; ⊤</code> in hypotheses and towards a ≠ ⊤` in the goal. But of course simp can't detect that.</p>",
